        "senses": ["darkvision 60 ft.", "passive Perception 12"],
        "languages": ["Giant"],
        "habitats": ["forest", "swamp", "hills", "caves"],
        "description": "<h2>Appearance</h2><p>A hulking, moss-covered brute that lopes through old-growth forests on knuckled fists, its rubbery green hide dappled with lichen and old scars. Standing nearly 9 feet tall, the Forest Troll is a study in ugly efficiency — all reach and muscle and hunger.</p><h2>The Regeneration Problem</h2><p>Forest Trolls are infamous for their ability to close wounds almost as fast as a blade can open them. Adventurers who have never faced one before are often horrified to watch a deep cut seal over in seconds. Only fire and acid leave wounds that truly stay open — a fact that separates experienced monster hunters from unlucky beginners.</p>",
